    "client_msg_id": "c5db9203-3b2e-438d-a6b3-972a769afecd",
    "text": "I'm not an expert, but I believe if you have a 3D matrix then you just multiply the point by it? Coordinate transformations are fundamentally matrix multiplications.\n\nSome other random thoughts:\n\n• The picture as drawn is not enough information, I believe. You need to specify the origin and directions of axes in both planes to get an unambiguous matrix. But if you already have a matrix this is moot.\n• A good first step is to transform the origin to the first plane.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1741225511.217169",
    "parent_user_id": "U0378MDUG1Y",
    "blocks": [
