  {
    "user": "U02E4DAQGSZ",
    "type": "message",
    "ts": "1741247463.216719",
    "client_msg_id": "0b63a5ef-841b-4310-a5a3-a4c5ff29f74a",
    "text": "so a 2d translation transform becomes becomes something like\n```[\n[1, 0, dx]\n[0, 1, dy]\n[0, 0,  1]\n]```\nits good to do the steps manually and you will see how the extra 1 hits the last column and manipulates the real coordinates directly.\n\nThe resultant of multiplying [x, y, 1] with the above transform is\n\n[x + dx, y + dy, 1] i.e. its original coordinate + dy, dy.",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1741225511.217169",
    "parent_user_id": "U0378MDUG1Y",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "5zXVU",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "so a 2d translation transform becomes becomes something like\n"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_preformatted",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "[\n[1, 0, dx]\n[0, 1, dy]\n[0, 0,  1]\n]"
              }
            ],
            "border": 0
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "its good to do the steps manually and you will see how the extra 1 hits the last column and manipulates the real coordinates directly.\n\nThe resultant of multiplying [x, y, 1] with the above transform is\n\n[x + dx, y + dy, 1] i.e. its original coordinate + dy, dy."
              }
            ]
          }
